# mister_de10nano_defconfig — P1.1 placeholder
#
# Deliberately minimal. This exists only to prove the BR2_EXTERNAL wiring
# (P1.1 acceptance: `make mister_de10nano_defconfig` + `make olddefconfig`
# succeed against this external tree from a clean checkout). It intentionally
# sets NO toolchain, architecture, kernel, or rootfs options — with nothing
# overridden here, Buildroot falls back to its own defaults (BR2_i386 +
# internal toolchain), which is a valid config that builds essentially
# nothing of interest. Real target settings (armv7-a/Cortex-A9/NEON-VFPv3/
# EABIhf/glibc, kernel, initramfs, package set) land in P1.2 onward — do not
# add them here without updating that task's plan.
#
# NOTE: `make savedefconfig` writes back to whatever BR2_DEFCONFIG was last
# loaded (standard Buildroot behavior) and only emits lines that diverge from
# kconfig defaults — since this config *is* the defaults, that will silently
# empty this file, including this comment block. That's expected; P1.2 is
# what gives this file real, savedefconfig-durable content.
